HEADWORD: Fallacious
<hw>Fal*la"cious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fallaciosus</ets>, fr. <ets>fallacia</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>fallacieux</ets>. See <er>Fallacy</er>.]</ety> <def>Embodying or
pertaining to a fallacy; illogical; fitted to deceive; misleading;
delusive; <as>as, <ex>fallacious</ex> arguments or reasoning</as>.</def>
-- <wordforms><wf>Fal*la"cious*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos>
-<wf>Fal*la"cious*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

